## சென்னைப் பல்கலைக்கழகத் தமிழ்ப் பேரகராதி
உக்கி
--
- ukki
- n. prob. உட்கு-.
- 1. A form of salutation, specially before Gaṇēša, consisting in the worshipper lowering and raising his body a certain number of times while folding his arms across his breast and holding his two ear lobes by the alternate hands;
- தோப்புக்கரணம். Loc.
- 2. A form of punishment;
- தண்டணைவகை. Loc.